timeline.bodyText:
In Firefox the error message is different: NetworkError when attempting to fetch resource.
This tells me that checking a message string is unreliable.
I’d suggest to check against the errors we throw ourselves instead:
if ((error instanceof EndpointResponseError) || (error instanceof EndpointError)) {
  // Error thrown in the client, carry to the user
  throw error;
} else {
  // Network error
  return this.cacheEndpointRequest({endpoint, methods, params});
}

This is safer: if it’s not the error we throw ourselves, then it’s a fetch error, which is only thrown for the network reasons.

